# Lab 3 - NumPy Operations

## Objective
To perform different NumPy operations and understand performance comparison.

## Tasks Performed
- Created 1D, 2D, and 3D arrays
- Performed indexing and slicing
- Reshaped arrays
- Applied mathematical operations
- Calculated statistical values (mean, median, std, percentiles)
- Performed linear algebra operations
- Generated random numbers
- Used temperature dataset
- Compared performance of Python list vs NumPy array

## Tools Used
- Python
- NumPy
- Jupyter Notebook / Google Colab

## Conclusion
NumPy provides efficient and fast operations for data processing compared to normal Python lists.
